value.0:
Ask around. Many people have odd jobs that need to be done, like rat extermination or running errands. Several members of House Zau'tar, among others, should have jobs for you.  Fragrin here to my left can help you get your bearings by sending you on a tour of our city, as well.

((Look for NPCs with green names around the city. These are quest-givers!))
Yes, they're the dominant Drow clan. They are spread all around L'Obsul. Just talk with them and see if they need something delivered.
Well, go to the duergar district and find the Duergar Peddler over there. He's willing to pay for proof of killing those vermin, like rats' ears. Truly hates the small beasts.

Well yes, if you're feeling well lucky, you can stop by "Good Stuffs". I must warn you however, its run by an Orog so don't expect anything good tasting.  A proper pub would be a lot better, but well... that's the closest thing we've got to one.
Depends on what you're looking for?
Look around the back side of the bazaar's northern wall.  There's some shady person around there who sells what you need.
Over in the svirfneblin district, look for the Sacred Pool - can't really miss it once you're there.  Near it is a fellow selling fine potions.
Head over to the svirfneblin district and go after the smell of fish. When you find  the fishmonger he'll also have a good supply of magicial supplies.
You can find Grumglesh in the bazaar nearby. He's got most things.
I am looking for some work, something that pays.
Thanks. I will go have a look around.
Do they have a decent place to get something to still the nerves with?
Where can I find some -hopefully cheap- equipment?
I am looking for a working crossbow.
I am looking for healing supplies.
I am looking for arms or armour.
